	Graduation from a New York State or Regionally accredited college or university with an Associate's Degree in Dental Hygiene.

OPEN COMPETITIVE
	Possession of a license to practice medicine in the State of New York, and; two years of training in general pathology, and; three years of training in neuropathology, or;
	Satisfactory equivalent combination of the above education and experience.

